the store to get some more.

42:31.590 --> 42:32.507
Wait a second.

42:32.675 --> 42:34.217
I'm on the way out the door.

42:34.343 --> 42:37.220
I just want to tell you I hope today is better.

42:38.180 --> 42:39.722
And that I love you.

42:39.890 --> 42:41.933
Damn it Jill those are just, those are words.

42:42.101 --> 42:43.643
They don't mean anything.

42:43.811 --> 42:44.769
Not now Jillian.

42:44.937 --> 42:46.062
I want this to be a good day.

42:46.230 --> 42:47.230
Just leave me alone.

42:48.107 --> 42:49.232
I love you.

42:51.235 --> 42:52.777
I think you were right about a lot of things.

42:53.237 --> 42:54.404
I love you.

42:54.572 --> 42:56.573
I want today to be peaceful.

42:57.783 --> 42:59.909
Damn it Jill, this is worthless.

43:03.497 --> 43:04.372
Ben.

43:04.540 --> 43:05.456
Now you want to talk?

43:05.624 --> 43:06.958
I'm way out the door Jill.

43:08.961 --> 43:09.877
I just want to say that...

43:10.045 --> 43:11.963
...I hope today is better.

43:12.631 --> 43:14.340
And that I love you.

43:14.508 --> 43:16.884
I want to believe you.

43:27.438 --> 43:29.731
Hey, while I'm at it I'll pick up that filter.

45:10.541 --> 45:12.750
Is it alright that I have that there?

45:12.918 --> 45:14.794
You going to fall down
if you don't have it there?

45:14.962 --> 45:16.587
Yeah, maybe.

45:21.885 --> 45:24.095
See this woman here with the knitting?

45:25.389 --> 45:28.391
She's a, she's a former Senator, right?

45:28.434 --> 45:32.145
Like a Nobel winner, but
her category is mittens.

45:32.730 --> 45:35.106
So she, she rides... what?

45:35.274 --> 45:35.898
You lost me.

45:36.066 --> 45:37.233
Just got a little too...

45:37.401 --> 45:37.942
Little?

45:38.110 --> 45:39.485
[Kris÷ Little cute, yeah.

45:39.653 --> 45:41.404
I don't know.
What do you have in mind?

45:41.447 --> 45:44.240
Alright, how about that guy?

45:44.408 --> 45:46.117
Tell me about him.

45:46.285 --> 45:48.619
He's divorced.

45:49.413 --> 45:51.539
Yeah, yep.

45:51.707 --> 45:54.625
Because she cheated.

45:55.544 --> 45:56.711
No?

45:57.504 --> 45:59.338
No. Oh, he did.

45:59.423 --> 46:00.423
He cheated.

46:01.175 --> 46:02.842
No. What was it?

46:03.010 --> 46:04.427
Alcoholic.

46:09.433 --> 46:12.935
Some substance of some kind.

46:14.438 --> 46:16.439
The illegal kind.

46:19.151 --> 46:20.735
I would think that there's some marriages

46:20.903 --> 46:23.404
that could survive something like that maybe.

46:23.447 --> 46:24.739
Maybe, but...

46:24.907 --> 46:25.740
Not yours?

46:25.908 --> 46:27.533
Not ours, no.

46:27.701 --> 46:29.494
From her perspective.

46:29.828 --> 46:32.455
I mean everything just flipped, you know.

46:32.456 --> 46:35.249
The guy she thought she married
turned out to be somebody else,

46:35.417 --> 46:37.460
a junkie, and uh...

46:37.628 --> 46:40.963
all the savings, all
the plans, everything resets.

46:41.131 --> 46:42.965
The lights turn on,

46:43.133 --> 46:46.135
and I'm holed up in some hotel across town.

46:49.473 --> 46:52.225
I have to open the store tomorrow.

46:53.977 --> 46:55.645
Not that early, I bet.

46:55.813 --> 46:58.481
No, I'm lucky to have that job.

46:59.274 --> 47:02.527
The sign store job you're lucky to have it?

47:07.491 --> 47:10.159
It's not my fault when it goes wrong.

47:13.205 --> 47:14.580
Yes it is.

